        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 24 at 3:25AM CDT by NWS Lake Charles LA</headline>
        <description>At 325 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Burkeville, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to vegetation and outdoor
objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Burkeville, Burr Ferry, Stringtown, Wiergate, Evans, and Newton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
